definitions.definition: ( intransitive ) To grow plump ; to swell out .
( transitive ) To make plump; to fill (out) or support; often with up .
examples: to plump oysters or scallops by placing them in fresh or brackish water

definitions.definition: ( intransitive ) To give a plumper (kind of vote).
( transitive ) To give (a vote), as a plumper.
( intransitive ) To favor or decide in favor of. [ with for ‘something’ ]

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To grow plump ; to swell out .

definitions.definition: To drop or fall suddenly or heavily, all at once.
To cast or let drop all at once, suddenly and heavily.
examples: to plump a stone into water

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To drop or fall suddenly or heavily, all at once.
